Installing Warlock
==================

Warlock builds with Meson and Ninja.


Dependencies
------------

Build tools:

  - meson
  - ninja
  - flex
  - bison
  - a C compiler (gcc or clang)
  - pkg-config

Libraries (development packages):

  - gtk+-3.0
  - glib-2.0
  - gio-2.0
  - gmodule-2.0

On Debian/Ubuntu:

  sudo apt install meson ninja-build flex bison build-essential \
      pkg-config libgtk-3-dev

On Fedora:

  sudo dnf install meson ninja-build flex bison gcc pkgconf-pkg-config \
      gtk3-devel


Building and installing
-----------------------

  meson setup build
  ninja -C build
  sudo ninja -C build install

This installs the `warlock' binary along with warlock.ui and the image
assets it loads at run time.  After installing, run:

  warlock


Build options
-------------

  - Install location (default /usr/local):

      meson setup build --prefix=/usr

  - Optimized build (the default build type is `debug', which makes GLib/GTK
    warnings fatal):

      meson setup build --buildtype=release

  To change an option after `meson setup' has already been run, use
  `meson configure', e.g.:

      meson configure build --buildtype=release

  then rebuild with `ninja -C build'.


Running from the build tree
---------------------------

The binary loads warlock.ui and its images from the install prefix, not from
the build tree, so you must install before the GUI will start.  For
development, install into a local prefix:

  meson setup build --prefix="$PWD/_install"
  ninja -C build install
  ./_install/bin/warlock

Re-run `ninja -C build install' after changing warlock.ui or any image;
code-only changes need only `ninja -C build'.


Configuration
-------------

User settings are stored in:

  ~/.config/warlock-gtk/warlock.ini

This file is created with sensible defaults on first run.
